The combined assets of Taiwan's offshorebanking units (obu) rose to 6.28 billion U.S. Dlrs at end-January from 6.21 billion in December and 6.34 billion inJanuary 1986, the central bank said.    A bank official told Reuters the increase came mainly fromincreased local obu borrowings from their Asian counterparts.    He said the assets, held by 15 foreign and local banks,were mainly in U.S. Dollars with the remainder in certificatesof deposit and bonds. About 90 pct of the assets came from Asiaand the rest from North America and Europe, he added. REUTER&#3;